<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>Long before vibe coding had a name I was joining every pre-alpha and beta for AI-assisted dev tools I could find. Alongside studying code, architecture and whatever was most reliable at the time, I built KRRRD: a tool that let users create simple websites and sophisticated card pages to present themselves online.</p>
    <p>You could generate from an image or screenshot, a URL with live parsing, plain text, or by cloning another user's public creation. Bring your own API key or use the KRRRD one. Manual editing was also there for text, images and colors.</p>
    <p>It never took off. No funding, no runway. But it taught me a solid 70% of what I know today and I am genuinely proud of it.</p>
